nl.tudelft.bw4t.message

Class BW4TMessage

  • java.lang.Object
    • nl.tudelft.bw4t.message.BW4TMessage

  • public class BW4TMessage
extends java.lang.Object
    Class containing all necessary information for a message Note that BW4TMessage objects are only used for direct agent communication within the BW4T server. This is totally separated from the GOAL messaging system.
    Author:
    trens

      • BW4TMessage

        public BW4TMessage(MessageType type,
                   java.lang.String room,
                   java.lang.String color,
                   java.lang.String playerId,
                   java.lang.Integer num)
        Create a new message
        Parameters:
        type - , the type of the message
        room - , the room that the message pertains to (Long.MAX_VALUE if message does not pertain to a room)
        color - , the color that the message pertains to (null if message does not pertain to a certain color)
        playerId - , the player that the message is directed to (null if message is not directed towards someone)
        num - is the number associated with the message.Typically number of blocks of given color in room. Nonsense value if the message does not use the number.
